|---|---|---|
| No security headers | Added `helmet()` | Prevents clickjacking, MIME sniffing, XSS via headers |
| No rate limiting | Added `express-rate-limit` | Mitigates DoS and brute-force attacks |
| No body size limit | `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })` | Prevents large-payload denial-of-service |
| Stack trace leakage | Global error handler hides details in production | Prevents information disclosure |
| No 404 handler | Explicit JSON 404 response | Prevents Express default HTML error pages |
| Server fingerprinting | `app.disable('x-powered-by')` | Hides Express from attackers (also covered by helmet) |
| Hardcoded port | `process.env.PORT \|\| 3000` | Enables flexible deployment |

### Required New Dependencies
```bash
npm install helmet express-rate-limit
```

